Basics:  Student Focus is alleged to have campaigned for the Fall 04 ASUCD Senate election in the Dorms. This is seen as a serious problem to some as it means they were campaigning closely to polling places on election day, which is against elections regulations. Some of the accusations include claims that the candidates helped people vote. Senators Nafeh Malik and Sean Ruel resigned only one week after they were sworn in.

